#week-title("One", "Review of Two Years: Taking Stock")

=== Core Teaching

Year Two ends with a full honest review of everything the student has
accomplished, attempted, and left unfinished across two years of systematic
alchemical study. This review is not a performance for the headmaster — it is
the practitioner's own assessment of where they genuinely stand.

The following questions frame the review:

*Laboratory:*
- Is the Plant Stone from Year One still progressing? What stage has it reached?
- Has the Archaeus of Water preparation (Year Two Month 1) reached completion,
  or is it still in an intermediate stage?
- What is the current state of the long circulation begun in Month 9?
- What active preparations remain unsealed and attending?
- What has been the most significant operative learning of Year Two?

*Inner Work:*
- Has the daily meditation practice been maintained with genuine consistency?
  Where did it falter, and what happened when it did?
- What has the Desoille work revealed that was not available at the beginning
  of Year One?
- How has the Tarot practice developed? Is it now a genuine diagnostic
  instrument or still primarily a study of correspondences?
- What has the somatic awareness and body-awareness practice opened?

*The Alchemical Journal:*
- Review the complete journal from both years. What patterns appear across
  time that were not visible from within the moment?
- What has changed in the practitioner's perception of nature, matter, and
  the Work?

This review takes whatever time it genuinely requires. It is not a checklist —
it is an alchemical calcination of the past two years, a burning away of
everything non-essential to reveal what the Salt of these years genuinely is.

=== Topics This Week

- Structured review of Year Two laboratory work: current state of all preparations
- Review of inner work consistency: honest assessment of practice quality
- Journal review: patterns visible across two years
- Identifying what is truly fixed (Salt) from the past two years of study

#inner-work[
  *The Two-Year Calcination*

  Sit with your complete alchemical journal for as long as is needed — an
  evening, a full day. Read it from the beginning. Do not edit, add, or
  correct. Simply witness.

  After reading, write one paragraph: what is the Salt of these two years?
  What has genuinely remained — what knowledge, what perception, what quality
  of attention — after everything transient has been burned away?
]

